Education Information: Beijing Compresses 2016 Junior High School Enrollment Proportion of Specialty Students - Xinhua News
On the 21st and 22nd, the Beijing Junior High School enrollment examination for special talents will be organized and implemented by the district education committees.
This year, all districts in Beijing have compressed the ratio of enrollment of special talents, making the competition more intense.
Taking Dongcheng District as an example, this year the proportion of elementary school students entering junior high school with special talents in the district is not more than 5% of the total enrollment plan in the region, with a planned enrollment of 380 people and a school enrollment ratio not exceeding 10% of the school's enrollment plan.
All students with physical, artistic, and scientific talents and who have registered online are eligible to participate in the examination for admission to the special talent program.
"To facilitate students' convenient participation in the examination, the Dongcheng District continues the examination arrangement of last year and sets 1-2 examination sites in each school district, a total of 13 examination sites. 
The examination sites are divided into examination rooms according to examination areas, and the examination periods are divided into hours. On the day of the examination, students will enter the examination site at different times in different examination areas for the examination. 
On May 23rd, the district education and admission examination center will publicly announce the list of students who have passed the examination on the internet, and students can check the examination results online."